tweet: For any Warren supporter whoâ€™s looking for a new home and would like to chat, my DMs are open. No matter what, it was in the spirit of her campaign that we will all vote to get Donald Trump out of the White House come November. Now we must, as @AOC said, #buildtogether.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: This race is not over. This fight is not over. And I believe we can sway opinion, change policies, and bring change to the White House by buckling down and fighting, arm in arm. We are better together. #NotMeUs

name: pfpicardi
tweet: At the same time, I encourage the Sanders supporters who hear those critiques to not brush them aside dismissively, but to reach out to folks one-on-one to let them know that this spirit is not what the campaign is about or represents.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: If we are truly better than this toxicity, we should work to change that perceptionâ€”by listening to the progressive women who support Sanders more intently than we do the trolls. I personally will be doing so by engaging in conversations about this matter OFF Twitter.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: It is a fact that women make up a significant base of Sandersâ€™ supporters, and many of those are women I respect greatly. I have listened to them when they said they feel erased by this narrativeâ€”by a toxic minority of men who shout loudly on Twitter.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: I know many Warren supporters are still licking their wounds. I have many friends who say they are wary of supporting Sanders because of the culture surrounding his campaign. I admit that I have also felt that, but I want to add something here.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: Thatâ€™s why I am voting for Senator @BernieSanders in the New York primary, and why I hope you will, too. A primary is the place to vote our valuesâ€”and on immigration, corruption, healthcare, and criminal justiceâ€”he represents the best of those forward-thinking values.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: Anyone who insists that we must â€œfall in lineâ€ one way or another is betraying our democratic process. This is still a primary! Sanders is still in this race! Primaries, regardless of who wins them, can help shape the electorate and the one who will eventually be elected!

name: pfpicardi
tweet: It would be disingenuous to say that I supported Warren for her policies and now choose to support anyone but Sanders. It is a fact that most of her policies ideologically align with those of @BernieSanders, and that he's been a champion of these ideals in American politics.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: But the results of Super Tuesday showed me that we need to align behind the candidate best suited for what will bring our country forward. @BernieSanders built a progressive coalitionâ€”a surge of American voters who are hoping for change in politics.

name: pfpicardi
tweet: But every vote is a vote earned, not a vote owed. I reject the notion that she didnâ€™t earn the right to see this race through to Super Tuesday. I also reject the notion that she has interrupted Sandersâ€™ momentumâ€”and the numbers show that. Warren deserved to fight.

name: pfpicardi
